FBIS3-23182 "jptot010__l94145" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY `Terrorists' Fire on Cizre District, Set Pipeline on Fire TA0403093694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 0800 GMT 4 Mar 94 TA0403093694 Ankara TRT Television Network Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over still of map] [Text] A group of terrorists fired on Sirnak's Cizre District with rocket launchers and long-barreled weapons last night. Our correspondent has learned that the shooting began at 2015 and lasted until 2300. Murat Orumcek, a policeman, was martyred, and another policeman was wounded. Some buildings were damaged. Meanwhile, terrorists attacked the BOTAS [Pipeline and Petroleum Transport Corporation] oil pipeline between Cizre and Idil. A fire erupted in the pipeline. Search operations are underway in the area. We have just received a report that Hincal Uluc, a correspondent with the daily SABAH, was walking in Levent in Istanbul when shots were fired at him at around 0930 from a passing car with the license plate 34 U 3115. Uluc was wounded in the foot and taken to a private hospital in Levent. An investigation is underway.
